---
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import siteConfig from '@/config/site.config';
---

<PageLayout
  title="FAQ"
  description="Frequently asked questions about VMFlux OBJ Exporter and the VMFlux product roadmap."
>
  <section class="border-b border-border bg-background">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16 lg:px-8">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">FAQ</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
        Frequently asked questions
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg text-foreground-muted">
        Quick answers about the current VMFlux exporter, support, downloads, and what is coming next.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-b border-border bg-muted/30">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-5 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid gap-4 text-sm font-semibold text-foreground md:grid-cols-4">
        <div>Current version: v3.2.6</div>
        <div>Supports Navisworks 2024 / 2025 / 2026</div>
        <div>OBJ + MTL available now</div>
        <div>Support by email</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-background">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16 lg:px-8">
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground">What does VMFlux support today?</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
            VMFlux currently focuses on OBJ + MTL export workflows for supported Navisworks versions.
            The current public release is VMFlux OBJ Exporter v3.2.6.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground">Which Navisworks versions are supported?</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
            The current exporter supports Navisworks 2024, 2025, and 2026.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground">What is coming next?</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
            GLB / glTF export and properties export are planned next as VMFlux expands into richer
            downstream workflows.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground">Can I download the plugin from this site?</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
            No. Downloads are handled through the Autodesk App Store, not through this website.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground">What does the exporter output?</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
            The current exporter outputs OBJ + MTL files, with material-aware behavior including
            real Navisworks material naming and transparency handling.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground">Can I export only part of a model?</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
            Yes. The exporter supports both Selected Models and Entire Model scope so you can export
            either a targeted subset or the full model.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground">What units does it support?</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
            The exporter supports mm, cm, m, km, in, ft, yd, and mi. It also includes
            “Keep numeric values (no unit scaling)” for workflows that need the original numeric values preserved.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground">How do I get support?</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
            Support is currently handled by email.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            <a
              href={`mailto:${siteConfig.email}`}
              class="text-base font-medium text-foreground hover:underline"
            >
              {siteConfig.email}
            </a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>